@startuml
title Workflow Version State Machine

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam roundcorner 5
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor lightblue
  BorderColor darkblue
  FontColor black
}

state "DRAFT" as Draft {
  [*] --> Draft : Create workflow version
  
  Draft : Can be edited ✓
  Draft : Can be deleted ✓
  Draft : Eligible for evaluation ✗
  Draft : is_current = false
}

state "PUBLISHED" as Published {
  Published : Immutable ✗
  Published : Cannot be deleted ✗
  Published : Eligible for evaluation ✓\n(if workflow.active = true)
  Published : is_current = true
}

state "ARCHIVED" as Archived {
  Archived : Immutable ✗
  Archived : Cannot be deleted ✗
  Archived : Eligible for evaluation ✗
  Archived : is_current = false
}

[*] --> Draft : POST /workflows\n(create new workflow)

Draft --> Draft : PUT /workflow-versions/{id}\n(edit rules/conditions)

Draft --> Published : POST /workflow-versions/{id}:publish\n(first publish)

Published --> Archived : POST /workflow-versions/{new_id}:publish\n(publish new version)

Draft --> [*] : DELETE /workflow-versions/{id}\n(delete draft only)

note right of Draft
  **DRAFT State**
  
  **Actions Allowed:**
  - Edit rules and conditions
  - Delete the version (hard delete)
  - Publish to make it active
  
  **Actions NOT Allowed:**
  - Cannot be used for evaluation
  - Cannot be archived directly
end note

note right of Published
  **PUBLISHED State**
  
  **Actions Allowed:**
  - Used for workflow evaluation\n  (only if workflow.active = true)
  - Can be activated/deactivated\n  (toggle workflow.active)
  - Can be viewed/exported
  - Can create new version (DRAFT)
  
  **Actions NOT Allowed:**
  - Cannot be edited (immutable)
  - Cannot be deleted
  - Cannot be directly archived
  (only archived when new version published)
  - Cannot "unpublish" or "set to draft"
end note

note right of Archived
  **ARCHIVED State**
  
  **Purpose:**
  - Maintains audit trail
  - Preserves historical decisions
  - Reference for change logs
  
  **Actions NOT Allowed:**
  - Cannot be edited
  - Cannot be deleted
  - Cannot be republished
  - Cannot be used for evaluation
end note

note bottom
  **State Transition Rules:**
  
  1. **DRAFT → PUBLISHED**: Only when publishing (one-way transition)
  2. **PUBLISHED → ARCHIVED**: Automatically when new version is published
  3. **DRAFT → [DELETED]**: Only draft versions can be deleted
  4. **ARCHIVED → [NO TRANSITIONS]**: Archived versions are immutable
  5. **PUBLISHED → DRAFT**: NOT POSSIBLE (must create new version)
  
  **Constraints:**
  - Only one PUBLISHED version per workflow (is_current=true)
  - Multiple ARCHIVED versions allowed per workflow
  - Version numbers are sequential and unique per workflow
  - Evaluation eligibility requires: PUBLISHED + workflow.active=true
  
  **Note:** The workflow entity has an `active` boolean field that controls
  evaluation eligibility independently of version status. This is separate
  from the version state machine shown above.
end note

@enduml


